Mafdet's harbor authority has received an unusual contract request from the Ventspeaker refugee diaspora community operating through the harbor's transit network: the community is requesting a formal elimination order against the ghost of Cairn-Mother Retha An, the Last Ventspeaker. Her spirit remains bound to the Oracle Ground in the Western Fold Approach, issuing prophetic pronouncements that the Ash Cult has been citing as endorsements for its territorial claims. With her ghost still operating, the Cult will continue to claim geological authority over the Speaking Vent. The harbor authority has accepted the request as a transit security matter, since Cult territorial claims block the Fold approach to the deeper volcanic zone mineral routes.
The last Ventspeaker's ghost has been laid to rest. Mafdet's harbor authority has notified the Ventspeaker refugee community, whose elders confirm they have received no further pronouncements from the Oracle Ground since your engagement. The Ash Cult has responded by claiming Retha An has achieved geological transcendence and now speaks through the Ventspeaker cult hierarchy directly — a theological maneuver that Midgaard's High Archive analysts are treating as an admission that her original ghost was, in fact, their primary legitimating authority.
